cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM

The paper proposes a quality measure for comparing solution sets generated by multiobjective optimizers. This topic falls under the field of optimization, which is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are all possible sub-categories that this paper could belong to. However, since the paper focuses on optimization and evolutionary algorithms, cs.NE is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible because they are related to optimization and machine learning.
